The evidence with the title 'Distribution of wealth - Wikipedia ' says According to the OECD in 2012 the top 0.6% of world population (consisting of adults with more than 1 million USD in assets ) or the 42 million richest people in the world held 39.3 % of world wealth. The next 4.4% (311 million people) held 32.3 % of world wealth. The bottom 95% held 28.4% of world wealth. The large gaps  ... 
